Minerals of Ukraine
By origin, minerals are divided into magmatic, sedimentary and metamorphic.
Therefore, their location is intimately related to the structure of the Earth's crust.
Fuel minerals of Ukraine.
Fuel minerals, mining in our state include: hard and brown coals, crude, natural gas, peat, oil shale.
The territory of Ukraine is rich in certain types of fuel minerals.
The state fully meets the own needs in hard and brown coal.
In the meantime, Ukraine is experiencing an acute shortage of crude and natural gas.
Practice has shown, that an acute shortage in anything may arise until we had a rational economy created in our country.
Peat in Ukraine long ago was mined in Polissia.
Since the mid-1990s it was used as a fuel only for local needs in the countryside, in the household, at factories in food, glass, porcelain and faience industry.
Various chemical substances are also obtained from peat, for example acetone, phenols, paraffin, forage, yeast.
Significant deposits of oil shale are in Cherkasy and Kirovograd regions.
Geography of the fuel minerals location is related to tectonic and geological structure of the territory.
Fuel minerals are of sedimentary origin and therefore are included in covers of an ancient and young platforms, as well as in edge foothill troughs.
Hard coals.
94.3% of coal deposits of our state are hard coals.
Ukrainian hard coals are of high quality.
Due to the high content of carbon, it has high calorific capacity.
Ukraine has deposits of the best grade of coal ‚Äì anthracite, the carbon content of which reaches 94-97%.
1/3 of coal is coking.
After special treatment, it is used in the smelting of cast-iron and steel.
In proven reserves of coal, Ukraine ranks VIII worldwide and I in Europe, and in mining, respectively, XI and III.
Proven coal reserves in Ukraine are about 50 billion tons.
Estimated reserves are about 120 billion tons.
